flowchart TB
    %% ========================================
    %% STRATEGY: DOCUMENTATION VALIDATION
    %% ========================================
    %% GOAL: Validate documentation completeness and accuracy through systematic testing.
    %% PROFILE: Planner-Component-DocumentationValidation
    %% COMPONENT_TYPE: Reusable validation component for documentation quality assurance
    %% USAGE: Incorporate into release workflows to ensure docs enable user success.
    %%
    %% CORE PRINCIPLE:
    %% Documentation length != Documentation quality.
    %% If the docs fail, the product fails.
    %%
    %% ORIGIN: GCPTOOLKIT-CONFIG-GAP-001 - 525 lines of documentation with 9 critical gaps
    %%
    %% INPUTS (expected from orchestrator):
    %% - documentation_path: Path to documentation being validated
    %% - user_journey: The workflow users should complete using docs
    %% - test_environment: Fresh environment for validation
    %%
    %% EXIT CONDITIONS:
    %% - Success: Blind-test agent completes all scenarios using only docs
    %% - Failure: Documentation gaps identified -> fix and retest
    %%
    %% CATCHES:
    %% - Missing steps
    %% - Incorrect steps
    %% - Ambiguous instructions
    %% - Undocumented prerequisites
    %% - Missing error recovery documentation
    %% - Inaccessible features

    %% ========================================
    %% PHASE 1: FOLLOW-DOCS-EXACTLY TEST
    %% ========================================
    %% Execute documentation step-by-step with zero prior knowledge
    DocValidationStart((Documentation Validation)) --> PrepareEnvironment[Prepare Fresh Environment
    - Clean slate, no prior setup
    - No cached knowledge
    - Standard user starting point]

    PrepareEnvironment --> BeginFollowTest[Begin Follow-Docs-Exactly Test
    - Start at line 1
    - Execute each step exactly as written
    - No interpretation or improvisation]

    BeginFollowTest --> ExecuteStep[Execute Current Step]

    ExecuteStep --> StepWorks{Step Works As Documented?}

    StepWorks -- "Yes" --> MoreSteps{More Steps?}
    MoreSteps -- "Yes" --> ExecuteStep
    MoreSteps -- "No" --> Phase1Pass[Phase 1 Complete]

    StepWorks -- "No" --> ClassifyGap{Gap Type?}

    ClassifyGap -- "Missing Step" --> RecordMissing[Record: Missing Step
    Document what step is needed]
    ClassifyGap -- "Incorrect Step" --> RecordIncorrect[Record: Incorrect Step
    Document expected vs actual]
    ClassifyGap -- "Ambiguous" --> RecordAmbiguous[Record: Ambiguous Instruction
    Document unclear language]
    ClassifyGap -- "Missing Prerequisite" --> RecordPrereq[Record: Undocumented Prerequisite
    Document required setup]
    ClassifyGap -- "No Error Recovery" --> RecordError[Record: Missing Error Recovery
    Document failure scenario]

    RecordMissing --> ContinueOrFail
    RecordIncorrect --> ContinueOrFail
    RecordAmbiguous --> ContinueOrFail
    RecordPrereq --> ContinueOrFail
    RecordError --> ContinueOrFail

    ContinueOrFail{Can Continue Testing?}
    ContinueOrFail -- "Yes: Workaround possible" --> ExecuteStep
    ContinueOrFail -- "No: Blocked" --> Phase1Blocked[Phase 1 Blocked
    Critical gaps found]

    %% ========================================
    %% PHASE 2: BLIND-TEST VALIDATION
    %% ========================================
    %% Agent with NO prior knowledge attempts user journey
    Phase1Pass --> StartBlindTest[Start Blind-Test Validation
    Spawn agent with:
    - NO prior system knowledge
    - Access ONLY to documentation
    - Target user journey to complete]

    StartBlindTest --> BlindExecute[Blind Agent Executes Journey]

    BlindExecute --> BlindSuccess{Agent Completes Journey?}

    BlindSuccess -- "Yes: All scenarios passed" --> ValidateCompleteness{All Requirements Met?}
    BlindSuccess -- "No: Agent failed/stuck" --> AnalyzeBlindFailure[Analyze Blind-Test Failure
    - Where did agent get stuck?
    - What information was missing?
    - What was unclear?]

    %% ========================================
    %% VALIDATION GATES
    %% ========================================
    ValidateCompleteness --> CheckCriteria{Success Criteria Check}

    CheckCriteria -- "Zero prior knowledge needed" --> CheckExact{Every step works exactly?}
    CheckExact -- "Yes" --> CheckUndocumented{No undocumented steps required?}
    CheckUndocumented -- "Yes" --> CheckManual{No manual file creation?}
    CheckManual -- "Yes" --> CheckRecovery{Error recovery documented?}
    CheckRecovery -- "Yes" --> ValidationPass((PASS: Documentation Valid))

    CheckExact -- "No" --> DocumentGaps
    CheckUndocumented -- "No" --> DocumentGaps
    CheckManual -- "No" --> DocumentGaps
    CheckRecovery -- "No" --> DocumentGaps

    %% ========================================
    %% FAILURE HANDLING
    %% ========================================
    AnalyzeBlindFailure --> DocumentGaps[Document All Gaps Found
    - Gap location
    - Gap description
    - Suggested fix]

    Phase1Blocked --> DocumentGaps

    DocumentGaps --> FixDocumentation[Fix Documentation
    Address all identified gaps]

    FixDocumentation --> RevalidateCheck{Re-validate Required?}
    RevalidateCheck -- "Yes" --> PrepareEnvironment
    RevalidateCheck -- "No: Minor fixes" --> ValidationPass

    %% ========================================
    %% RELEASE INTEGRATION
    %% ========================================
    %% See: docs/testing/pre_release_checklist.md
    %% - Phase 7: Follow-docs-exactly test
    %% - Phase 7b: Blind-test validation
    %% - Must pass before documentation sign-off
    %% - Phase 12: Final documentation loop

    %% ========================================
    %% STYLING
    %% ========================================
    classDef entrypoint fill:#90EE90,stroke:#228B22
    classDef exitpoint fill:#FFB6C1,stroke:#DC143C
    classDef successpoint fill:#98FB98,stroke:#006400
    classDef critical fill:#FFD700,stroke:#FF8C00
    classDef recording fill:#DDA0DD,stroke:#8B008B

    class DocValidationStart entrypoint
    class ValidationPass successpoint
    class BeginFollowTest,StartBlindTest critical
    class RecordMissing,RecordIncorrect,RecordAmbiguous,RecordPrereq,RecordError recording
